{#-
  Alert — inline status banner with optional dismiss + action.

  Communicates status (info / warning / danger / success) to the user.
  NOT a modal: Alert is a persistent inline surface, scoped to its parent
  region. For blocking confirmations with focus-trap, see the Ring 2
  `Dialog` (and `AlertDialog`) compound.

  Tones:
    - soft (default) — `*-soft` bg + `*-soft-foreground` text + 1px border.
                       Lower visual weight, suitable for long-running banners
                       and inline form-level errors.
    - solid          — `*` bg + `*-foreground` text, no border. Higher
                       emphasis — page-level critical announcements.

  Variants → default icon + default role:
    info     → info             icon  · role="status"
    warning  → alert-triangle   icon  · role="status"
    danger   → alert-circle     icon  · role="alert"   (assertive live region)
    success  → check            icon  · role="status"

  Doctrine (OQ-15):
    Dismiss is a minimal Stimulus controller `alert-dismiss` (~12 lines).
    `<dialog>` is rejected — Alert is inline status, NOT modal. Dialog
    would force focus-trap + backdrop, inadequate for a banner.

  Animation:
    appear  — opacity 0 → 1 + translateY(-4px) → 0, 180 ms emphasized
              (subtle, no bump). Fires on mount via CSS animation.
    dismiss — opacity 1 → 0, 120 ms accelerate. Triggered by controller
              stamping data-state="dismissing"; transitionend removes
              the element from the DOM.

  Parameters:
    variant            (string, optional) — info (default) | warning | danger | success
    tone               (string, optional) — soft (default) | solid
    title              (string, optional) — bold heading line
    body               (string, optional) — shorthand for a simple paragraph
                                            body. Mutually exclusive with the
                                            `body` block (block wins if defined).
    icon               (string, optional) — Lucide icon override; defaults
                                            to the variant icon (see map).
    hideIcon           (bool,   optional) — false (default). true → no icon.
    dismissible        (bool,   optional) — false (default). true → trailing
                                            dismiss button + `alert-dismiss`
                                            controller wired.
    dismissAriaLabel   (string, optional) — accessible name for the dismiss
                                            button. Required when dismissible.
    dismissMessage     (string, optional) — i18n key passed to the controller
                                            for the SR announcement on dismiss
                                            (default: 'theme.alert.aria.dismissed').
    htmlId             (string, optional) — auto-generated if absent.
    roleOverride       (string, optional) — alert | status. Defaults to alert
                                            for danger, status otherwise.
    className          (string, optional) — extra utility classes on the root.

  Blocks (both optional):
    body   — rich body content (paragraphs, links inside). Takes precedence
             over the `body` string parameter.
    action — trailing inline action slot (typically a ghost-variant Button).
-#}

{%- set variant          = variant          | default('info') -%}
{%- set tone             = tone             | default('soft') -%}
{%- set title            = title            | default(null) -%}
{%- set body             = body             | default(null) -%}
{%- set icon             = icon             | default(null) -%}
{%- set hideIcon         = hideIcon         | default(false) -%}
{%- set dismissible      = dismissible      | default(false) -%}
{%- set dismissAriaLabel = dismissAriaLabel | default(null) -%}
{%- set dismissMessage   = dismissMessage   | default('theme.alert.aria.dismissed') -%}
{%- set htmlId           = htmlId           | default('theme-alert-' ~ random()) -%}
{%- set roleOverride     = roleOverride     | default(null) -%}
{%- set className        = className        | default('') -%}

{%- set _iconMap = {
  'info':    'info',
  'warning': 'alert-triangle',
  'danger':  'alert-circle',
  'success': 'check',
} -%}
{%- set _effectiveIcon = icon ?? _iconMap[variant] -%}
{%- set _role = roleOverride ?? (variant == 'danger' ? 'alert' : 'status') -%}

{%- set _classes = ['theme-alert'] -%}
{%- if className -%}{%- set _classes = _classes | merge([className]) -%}{%- endif -%}

<div
  class="{{ _classes | join(' ') }}"
  id="{{ htmlId }}"
  role="{{ _role }}"
  data-variant="{{ variant }}"
  data-tone="{{ tone }}"
  {%- if dismissible %}
    data-controller="alert-dismiss"
    data-alert-dismiss-message-value="{{ dismissMessage }}"
  {%- endif %}
>
  {%- if not hideIcon -%}
    {% include '@theme/components/icon/icon.html.twig' with {
      name: _effectiveIcon,
      decorative: true,
      size: 'md',
      className: 'theme-alert__icon',
    } %}
  {%- endif -%}

  <div class="theme-alert__content">
    {%- if title -%}
      <p class="theme-alert__title">{{ title }}</p>
    {%- endif -%}
    {%- if block('body') is defined and block('body') is not empty -%}
      <div class="theme-alert__body">{%- block body -%}{%- endblock -%}</div>
    {%- elseif body -%}
      <div class="theme-alert__body"><p>{{ body }}</p></div>
    {%- endif -%}
    {%- if block('action') is defined and block('action') is not empty -%}
      <div class="theme-alert__actions">{%- block action -%}{%- endblock -%}</div>
    {%- endif -%}
  </div>

  {%- if dismissible -%}
    <button
      type="button"
      class="theme-alert__dismiss"
      aria-label="{{ dismissAriaLabel }}"
      data-action="click->alert-dismiss#dismiss"
    >
      {% include '@theme/components/icon/icon.html.twig' with {
        name: 'x',
        decorative: true,
        size: 'sm',
      } %}
    </button>
  {%- endif -%}
</div>
